<s> [INST] You are an expert in Natural Language Inference (NLI). Please list all possible explanations why the the following statement is true (entailment) given the context below without introductory phrases. 
Context: Even analysts who had argued for loosening the old standards, by which the market was clearly overvalued, now think it has maxed out for a while. 
Statement: Some analysts wanted to make the old standards less restrictive for investors. 
Answer: [/INST] 1. The analysts held the view that the market was overvalued according to the old standards.
2. The analysts proposed changing the strictness of the old standards to make them more lenient.
3. The analysts thought that the old standards were too restrictive for investors.
4. The analysts suggested loosening the old standards to allow for more flexibility.
5. The analysts believed that the market could benefit from a relaxation of the old standards.
6. The analysts advocated for a modification of the old standards to make them less stringent.
7. The analysts contended that the market was undervalued when considering more flexible standards.
8. The analysts urged for a reevaluation of the old standards to better reflect market conditions.
9. The analysts proposed to adjust the old standards to better suit the market situation.
10. The analysts recommended a change in the old standards to make them less strict.</s>